cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with semantic image segmentation, which is a computer vision task, and specifically focuses on using deep neural networks for this purpose. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel approach for selecting hidden units in the neural network, which involves stochastic inference, and this falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on the Pascal VOC 2012 benchmark, which is a widely used dataset in multimedia (cs.MM).
